{
  "name": "REC | Get New/Updated CEE Leads | 1 of 3",
  "description": "This recipe automates the process of updating or creating campaign members in Salesforce based on new or updated leads from the CEE Lead custom object.\n\n- The process begins by getting details for new or updated leads in Salesforce, filtering out any deleted records.\n- For each valid lead, it searches for existing contacts in Salesforce using the provided email. If no contacts are found or if they are marked as deleted, it proceeds to check for existing leads.\n- If no valid leads are found, the recipe creates a new lead in Salesforce with the provided details and associates it with a campaign member, marking the status as \"Engaged.\"\n- If a lead already exists, it checks for associated campaign members. If none are found or if they are deleted, it creates a new campaign member for the existing lead. If a campaign member exists, it updates the member's information instead.\n- The recipe also handles additional information and updates the lead's description as necessary.\n- In case of any errors during execution, the recipe logs the error details for troubleshooting.\n\nOverall, this recipe streamlines the process of creating and updating leads and campaign members in Salesforce, ensuring that the data remains current and accurate.",
